{"body": "I think that ```random()``` and ```sample(n)``` methods are natural extensions and could be useful as people keep implementing them in inefficient ways. And if they do, a database-specific function like ```rand()``` is used.\n\nAbout the context where this could be used: recently I needed to present random suggestions for users. Other uses I can think of: showing random quote, ad banner, friend suggestion(s)..", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6825892", "created_at": "2012-07-07T19:37:43Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7001#issuecomment-6825892", "updated_at": "2012-07-07T19:37:43Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7001, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/sheerun", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/306b63b79c78a1b67e1789790ad2db86?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbf0634d99fd0aaad6eef6ddda503ee38.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/received_events", "gravatar_id": "306b63b79c78a1b67e1789790ad2db86", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "sheerun", "type": "User", "id": 292365, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheerun/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523800f4bd3543c15100c08b"}, "id": 6825892, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7001"}
